==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ambiguous
<hw>Am*big"u*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ambiguus</ets>, fr. <ets>ambigere</ets> to wander about, waver;
<ets>amb-</ets> + <ets>agere</ets> to drive.]</ety> <def>Doubtful or
uncertain, particularly in respect to signification; capable of being
understood in either of two or more possible senses; equivocal; <as>as,
an <ex>ambiguous</ex> course; an <ex>ambiguous</ex>
expression.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What have been thy answers? What but dark,⟦br⟧
<qex>Ambiguous</qex>, and with double sense deluding?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Doubtful; dubious; uncertain; unsettled;
indistinct; indeterminate; indefinite. See <er>Equivocal</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambiguously</ent>⟦br⟧
